Lavern
Copyright 2025-2026 Antti Innanen.
Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
https://github.com/AnttiHero/lavern

Ten specialist-agent system prompts are lifted from Lavern's
`src/agents/prompts/` directory and adapted (per ADR-072) into the
Oscar LLP firm-mode at `ui/desktop/src/components/oscar/oscar-llp/`
(originally landed as "Lavern firm-mode" Sprint 21; rebranded to
"Oscar LLP" Sprint 24-A per ADR-078, with "Lavern" reserved for
upstream-credit pipeline attribution). Sprint 21 pulled at:

  Upstream commit: 7c2efe61524b
  Upstream date:   2026-05-20
  Pull date:       2026-05-20

Source prompts (Lavern slug → Oscar GC partner name):
  ma-specialist        → Sarah Chen (M&A)
  contract-specialist  → Marcus Webb (Commercial Contracts)
  litigation-partner   → Daniel Reeves (Litigation)
  employment-counsel   → Priya Patel (Employment)
  ip-specialist        → James Okafor (IP)
  tax-counsel          → Helena Voss (Tax)
  privacy-counsel      → Diana Park (Privacy)
  capital-markets      → Robert Sinclair (Capital Markets)
  tech-transactions    → Aisha Khan (Tech Transactions)
  regulatory-counsel   → Thomas Schmidt (Regulatory)

Adapted to remove Lavern-internal orchestration substrate (debate-board
postings, evaluator-gate JSON output, personality numerics). Persona
voice and multi-phase analysis frameworks preserved verbatim. Verbatim
raw originals are checked in at
`ui/desktop/src/components/oscar/oscar-llp/prompts/raw/<slug>.ts.original`
for diff-against-upstream review.

Per-file provenance comments appear at the top of each adapted prompt
file (`Lifted from github.com/AnttiHero/lavern (Apache 2.0, HEAD
7c2efe61524b) src/agents/prompts/<slug>.ts. Adapted per ADR-072: ...`).

Trademark notice: "Lavern" is the name of Antti Innanen's project. Per
Apache License 2.0 §6, this NOTICE file describes the origin of the
vendored content; the mark is referenced openly in Oscar GC's NOTICE and
provenance comments to credit the upstream design (per the Sprint 21
brief's "no hiding" framing). Sprint 24-A (ADR-078) reframes the
partner-roster UI surface as "Oscar LLP" (Oscar GC's invented bench) and
reserves the "Lavern" name for the upstream-credit pipeline port arriving
in Sprint 24-B+C — the substance Lavern's own evals validated. The
"Lavern" mark is not used to imply endorsement.

